AWSTemplateFormatVersion: Versions to identify the capabilities of the template 
Description		: Description about the details of the templates(consequent resources)
Metadata(optional)	: Customizes and provide details about the template and also installs the applications for each resource
Parameters(optional)	: enables us to input custom values to the template each time we create or update a stack
Rules(optional)		: used to validate a set parameters passed to the template during stack creation 
Mappings(optional)	: matches the key to a corresponding set of values in a mapped list or dict
Conditions(optional)	: describe the circumstances under which the entities are created or configured
Transform(optional)	: specifies one or more macros that AWS CloudFormation uses to process the template
Resources		: declares the AWS resources that you want to include in the stack
Outputs(optional)	: declares output values that you can import into other stacks, return in response or view on the AWS CFT
